A nice place to grab a quick healthy bite! Their offerings are mostly vegetarian, a few vegan options, and a few meat options for the carnivores. Their concept is lots and lots of vegetables with whatever else you may want with them.  I opted to do a custom warm veggie bowl. The lady helping me was knowledgeable in what was vegan and she was able to ask someone to double-check about things being gluten-free before she included them in my order. For the warm veggie bowl, you can pick four vegetables which they then blanch. While waiting for that, you pick a base (quinoa, rice, greens, or lentils), a base sauce (black bean, cilantro, spicy tomato, green curry, garlic yogurt), option for meat or a premium add-on (avocado, egg, mozzarella), fresh veggie toppings, a dressing, and a crunchy topping if you so desire.  I would say that the portions of each item was pretty small, but you can have so many different items that they all add up to be a pretty substantial meal. I had no problem making my custom bowl vegan and gluten-free and it tasted DELICIOUS. Just a couple more vegan options would be nice, but I would absolutely come back and try a different combination of veggies!

I love a good innovative restaurant especially one from DC celebrity chef Jose Andres. Beefsteak is a Jose's first fast casual restaurant and one where he gets to show his funny side. First off, Beefsteak is a vegetable based fast casual restaurant. All the plates are veggies based (you can add an egg, salmon, or chicken to any dish for all the meat lovers).  Secondly, the decorations are super quirky in an inviting way. There are quirky tables everywhere with Beefsteak's quirky Cartoon Network esque egg plant of a logo everywhere.  I tried the Naked bowl and it was great! As you get your drink (they have juices, Honest Tea, Bold Rock cider, and free basil and cucumber infused ice water) there are a few oils and sauces you can put on your meal which makes the flavors pop!  One thing I noticed is there are plug ins everywhere, which is smart since Beefsteak is right in the heart of George Washington University's campus!

What is the concept of this restaurant? They have Asian sauces, with Mediterranean chicken (which has absolutely a disgusting taste), with salad bar concept. At the end, they charge you for every single item you add to your bowl. My bowl ended up being $17  while I take the same bowl from sweet green for $10.
